      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2020-08-04</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2020-09-23T18:41:41Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Assisting Teachers and Home Office Modernization for Employees Act or the AT HOME Act</b></p> <p>This bill allows employers who have not more than 150 full-time employees a tax credit for 25% of their qualified remote work expenses. The bill defines <i>qualified remote work</i> <i>expenses</i> as expenses paid or incurred to allow employees to work from a worksite other than a shared office space, that are necessary to allow for continuation of normal business functions, are in response to COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019), and occur after February 15, 2020, and before January 1, 2021. The bill also extends such tax credit to tax-exempt entities. </p> <p>The bill also allows an income-based tax deduction for remote work expenses. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
